Documents the model-adapter layer that bridges `ctx-summarize`'s provider-agnostic `Agent` seam to a concrete LLM. Not a source file with logic to trace, but a spec/contract others must follow — treat it as authoritative for what adapter scripts must do.

Key facts an editor needs: adapters are standalone scripts (not Rust, not linted), invoked via `$CTX_AGENT_CMD` through `sh -c`. Contract is strict — stdin is `{"system": <string>, "user": <string>}` JSON, stdout must be *only* the completion text verbatim, exit non-zero on any failure or empty output (empty output must not exit 0, since the runner treats non-zero as the sole error signal). Adapters must be pure transport: no reformatting, no added instructions — behavior lives entirely in the prompt files (`prompts/summarizer-leaf.md`, `prompts/summarizer-rollup.md`), which is what keeps adapters swappable across model providers.

The reference implementation is `summarizer-claude.py` (stdlib-only Anthropic Messages API client, no pip deps), configured via `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`, `CTX_AGENT_MODEL`, `CTX_AGENT_MAX_TOKENS`, `CTX_AGENT_TEMPERATURE`, `ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL`. It caches the system prompt block (identical across all leaf/rollup calls in one task) for cost/latency, and pins reasoning to minimum effort since this task doesn't benefit from extended thinking — if either of those choices is changed, cost/latency will regress.

Adding a new provider means dropping a sibling script honoring the same contract and pointing `CTX_AGENT_CMD` at it — no Rust-side changes are expected; if a change here requires touching the Rust core, that's a sign the decoupling has been violated.